## Lessons Already Learned (Do Not Repeat These Mistakes)

1. `friendly_id` with `:history` — always
2. Virtual attributes don't get `_changed?` — check underlying columns
3. Always add `should_generate_new_friendly_id?`
4. `record.reload` before asserting path after slug-changing update
5. `"nil"` ≠ `nil` in factory data
6. `rails runner` shell quoting — use console or temp file
7. `display_date` — build manually when fields are optional
8. `NULLS LAST` for optional-field ordering
9. `shoulda-matchers` + `in: range` — use explicit `greater_than_or_equal_to` / `less_than_or_equal_to`
10. Never ship generator-default factories
11. Delete generator stubs immediately
12. `page.text.index` for ordering assertions, not CSS selectors
13. Git hooks must be opted into after cloning (`git config core.hooksPath .githooks`)
14. `fetch-depth: 0` required in GitHub Actions for commit history
15. Merge `main` into feature branch before opening PR, not after

